In [10]:
cell_totals = []
spot_density_totals = []
gran1_means = []
gran2_means = []
gran3_means = []
gran5_means = []
gran7_means = []
n2_avg_totals = []

df_export = pd.DataFrame(
    columns=(
        'well', 'content', 'total_cells', 'total_density', 'gran1_means', 'gran2_means',
        'gran3_means', 'gran5_means', 'gran7_means', 'n2_avg_totals'
    ))

for well in sorted(agg_spot_features.keys()):
    if len(agg_spot_features[well]) != 0:
        cell_totals.append(len(agg_spot_features[well]))
        spot_density_totals.append(np.mean(agg_density_features[well]))
        gran1_means.append(np.mean(agg_gran1_features[well]))
        gran2_means.append(np.mean(agg_gran2_features[well]))
        gran3_means.append(np.mean(agg_gran3_features[well]))
        gran5_means.append(np.mean(agg_gran5_features[well]))
        gran7_means.append(np.mean(agg_gran7_features[well]))
        n2_avg_totals.append(np.mean(agg_n2_avg_features[well]))

        content = fr.get_well_property(metadata, well, 'Content')
        df_export = df_export.append(
            {'well' : well,
             'content' : content,
             'total_cells' : cell_totals[-1],
             'total_density' : spot_density_totals[-1],
             'gran1_means' : gran1_means[-1],
             'gran2_means' : gran2_means[-1],
             'gran3_means' : gran3_means[-1],
             'gran5_means' : gran5_means[-1],
             'gran7_means' : gran7_means[-1],
             'n2_avg_totals' : n2_avg_totals[-1]}, ignore_index=True)
    else:
        print 'Empty well: %s (%s)' % (well,
            np.array(metadata[metadata['Well'] == well[0] + ' - ' + well[1:]]['Content'])[0])

df_export.to_csv(os.path.join(output, 'totals_mda231.tsv'), sep='\t', index=False)

 """
Identify outlier (i.e. point with greatest perpendicular distance to trendline 
i.e. dy/dx much lower than trendline gradient)
"""
for well in agg_spot_features.keys():
    if len(agg_density_features[well]) > 0 and len(agg_gran2_features[well]) > 0:
        density = np.mean(agg_density_features[well])
        granulometry = np.mean(agg_gran2_features[well])
        dydx = granulometry / density
        if dydx < 10:
            print 'Well: %s\nSpot density: %.04f\nAverage granulometry: %.04f' % (well, density, granulometry)

well = 'G17'

channel = 'tertiary__expanded'
feature = 'spotfeatures_count'

fig = plt.figure()

for field in all_features[well]:
    for index, _ in enumerate(all_features[well][field]['roisize']):
        gran_2_feature = all_features[well][field]['granu_open_volume_2'][index]
        roi_feature = all_features[well][field]['roisize'][index]
        spot_count_feature = all_features[well][field]['spotfeatures_count'][index]
        
        spot_density_feature = spot_count_feature / roi_feature
        dydx =  gran_2_feature / spot_density_feature

        if dydx < 3.5:
            ic = ImageCropper(well, field, ch5_folder, plate)
            bounding_boxes = ic.get_bounding_box_list(channel)
            ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1)
            ic.plot_bounding_box(ax, ic.extract_bounding_box(bounding_boxes[index]),
                                 title='Low density, high gran.')
        if dydx > 7:
            ic = ImageCropper(well, field, ch5_folder, plate)
            bounding_boxes = ic.get_bounding_box_list(channel)
            ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2)
            ic.plot_bounding_box(ax, ic.extract_bounding_box(bounding_boxes[index]),
                                 title='High density, low gran.')

fig.set_figheight(7.5)
fig.set_figwidth(10)
plt.show()

The curve artefacts at the base of the cloud are the result of computing spot density on cells with a single spot, two spots, etc., giving density = $\frac{1}{area}$, $\frac{2}{area}$, etc. as area is fairly constant across cells.

ranks = (0, 5)
ranked_wells = sorted(compare_wells, key=lambda well: np.median(agg_spot_features[well]), reverse=True)

# Collect top ranked wells
top_wells = ranked_wells[ranks[0]:ranks[1]]
top_wells_content = [fr.get_well_property(metadata, well, 'Content')[0:5] for well in top_wells]
top_wells_features = [agg_spot_features[well] for well in top_wells]
colours = ['blue']*len(top_wells)

# Append specific wells
top_wells.extend(['Negative', 'None'])
top_wells_content.extend(['DMSO', 'None'])
top_wells_features.extend([dmso_pool_spot_features, none_pool_spot_features])
colours.extend(['red', 'gray'])

p_values = [stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_spot_features, features) for features in top_wells_features]
tick_labels = ['%s %s \np = %.2E' % (well, top_wells_content[i], p_values[i]) for i, well in enumerate(top_wells)]

fp = FeaturePlotter()
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 7.5))

fp.plot_box(ax, features=top_wells_features, tick_labels=tick_labels, colours=colours,
            title='Spot count %s - %s vs Negative, Null' % (ranks[0] + 1, ranks[1]),
            xlabel='well - content - p-value',
            ylabel='spot count')
ax.set_ylim([0, 100])

non_empty_wells = filter(lambda well: not not agg_spot_features[well], agg_spot_features.keys())
compare_wells = filter(lambda well: not well in dmso_wells and not well in none, non_empty_wells)

BONFERRONI_THRESHOLD = stats.P_VALUE_THRESHOLD / len(compare_wells)

Here we rank those experiments with a statistically significant p-value, adjusting for multiple testing with a Bonferroni correction.

In [34]:
"""
Display significant results
"""
df = pd.DataFrame(columns=('Well', 
                           'Content',
                           'P-score(count)',
                           'P-score(density)',
                           'P-score(gran2)',
                           'P-score(n2avg)'))

for i, well in enumerate(compare_wells):
    p_score_spots = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_spot_features, agg_spot_features[well])
    p_score_density = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_density_features, agg_density_features[well])
    p_score_gran2 = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_gran2_features, agg_gran2_features[well])
    p_score_n2avg = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_n2_avg_features, agg_n2_avg_features[well])

    content = np.array(metadata[metadata['Well'] == well[0] + ' - ' + well[1:]]['Content'])[0]
    df.loc[i] = [well, content, p_score_spots, p_score_density, p_score_gran2, p_score_n2avg]

Where $B$ is the distribution of double strand breaks in the well, $D$ is the amount of cell death, $C$ is the ultimate cell count and $P$ is the p-value statistic calculated in the analysis. The structure renders $B$ a confounder, hence it must be conditioned on prior to analysis. As a continuous-valued variable, it must be thresholded somehow, the simplest approach being a binary threshold.

"""
Display significant results for low cell count
"""
df = pd.DataFrame(columns=('Well', 'Content', 'P-score(count)', 'P-score(density)', 'P-score(n2avg)'))

for i, well in enumerate(low_cell_count_wells):
    p_score_spots = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_spot_features, agg_spot_features[well])
    p_score_density = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_density_features, agg_density_features[well])
    p_score_n2avg = stats.kolgomorov_smirnov(dmso_pool_n2_avg_features, agg_n2_avg_features[well])

    content = np.array(metadata[metadata['Well'] == well[0] + ' - ' + well[1:]]['Content'])[0]
    df.loc[i] = [well, content, p_score_spots, p_score_density, p_score_n2avg]
    
print '<Spot count>'
df_sorted = df.sort_values('P-score(count)', ascending=True)
print df_sorted[df_sorted['P-score(count)'] < LOW_CELL_BONFERRONI_THRESHOLD][['Well', 'Content', 'P-score(count)']]

print '\n<Spot count (Benjamini-Hochberg adjustment)>'
k = stats.benjamini_hochberg(df_sorted['P-score(count)'].as_matrix())
print df_sorted.iloc[0:k][['Well', 'Content', 'P-score(count)']]
